{
  "stem": "1918.6",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And every once in a while, we knew people who were with us in Auschwitz or from even my hometown.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we found out that this one is alive and that one is alive.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we walked for two weeks.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we reached Oelsk, and there, indeed, was a train.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it was a war-torn land of war machinery that was shot up probably, and it took us two weeks.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "All the liberated people from all over the world who were liberated by now, soldiers from every part of the world.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the Russians put us on these trains, and they made food for us whenever they can get-- could get some food.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the rails were so shot up that it took us two weeks to get to Odessa, and it was only 1,000 kilometers away.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We probably should have made it  in less than a day, and it was two weeks.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we got there, and there was a big displacement center of some kind.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they ostensibly sent everybody home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now, we wouldn't go home to Hungary.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We knew there was nothing waiting for us there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the only person who we are quite sure is alive is our father, and he's in America.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we want to go to America.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And a British flyer who spoke Yiddish heard our story.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he was so moved by it that he immediately went to see the American attache or consul, or whoever he was, and told him our story.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we told him some of our story. and we were-- he made an appointment for us for the next morning at 9 o'clock, and he took the three of us there.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And he was the trans-- he spoke Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
